<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,1156,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<bibRefCitation author="Besch" box="[312,484,1196,1222]" pageId="12" pageNumber="22" refString="Besch, W. (1963 a) Sudandine Limnesiiden. Acarologia, 5, 259 - 265." type="journal article" year="1963" yearSuffix="a">
Besch (
<number box="[401,461,1196,1222]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1963.0">1963</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName box="[659,908,1196,1221]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis box="[659,908,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Limnesia patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Ribaga" authorityName="Ribaga" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="minuscula" subSpecies="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[978,1262,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. minuscula minuscula</emphasis>
Ribaga
</taxonomicName>
, but this was not followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[662,803,1236,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1980) Studies on neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 31, 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">
Cook (
<number box="[741,803,1236,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1980.1988">1980</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[816,879,1236,1262]" pageId="12" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1988) Water mites from Chile. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 42, 1 - 356." type="journal article" year="1988">1988</bibRefCitation>
). The specimens from this study have separated first coxal plates, and their IV­leg­ 
<number box="[806,820,1276,1302]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="6.0">6</number>
have six swimming setae. Therefore it is assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[406,571,1316,1341]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis box="[406,571,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[759,913,1316,1341]" class="Arachnida" family="Limnesiidae" genus="Limnesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuscula">
<emphasis box="[759,913,1316,1341]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">L. minuscula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with swimming setae on IV­leg­ 
<number box="[1309,1323,1316,1342]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="6.0">6</number>
have fused first coxal plates. The specimens collected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[935,1083,1356,1382]" pageId="12" pageNumber="22" refString="Cook, D. R. (1980) Studies on neotropical water mites. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 31, 1 - 645." type="journal article" year="1980">
Cook (
<number box="[1014,1075,1356,1382]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="1980.0">1980</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
have 
<number box="[1153,1192,1356,1382]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2­4</number>
swimming setae on IV­leg­ 
<number box="[457,471,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="6.0">6</number>
.
</paragraph>
